Server side visibility condition to determine when the Add Component command can be visible. Works by checking the preference values for the supported open types for each CAD application. There will be additional client side visibility conditions associated as well, such as to determine if Active Workspace is running in the hosted mode, before the command is made visible.

This condition hides the Cut command for the objects of type Alternate ID.

Server side command visibility condition for Assign Projects command. This command should be visible only if selected object is of type WorkspaceObject, Dataset or Form. This command should not be visible if selected object is of type EPMTask or Signoff. This command should not be visible if assignable_projects property is not defined for logged in user.

Server side command visibility condition for Assign Projects command. This command should be visible for Teamcenter version >=10.1.5 and <=11.2.3. This command should be visible only if selected object is of type WorkspaceObject, Dataset or Form. This command should not be visible if selected object is of type EPMTask or Signoff. This command should not be visible if assignable_projects property is not defined for logged in user.

This condition determines if ownership of instances of a particular business object type can be changed.

This condition determines if instances of a particular business object type can be checked-in at current site.

This condition determines if instances of a particular business object type can be checked-out. This depends upon the following checks: if the type is checkout-able; if the instance is modifiable at the current site.

This condition determines if the requested object type is allowed to be deleted.
This condition determines if a selected saved search is not null.
This condition is designed to check if the command is visible if the selected object is an ACE object. The ACE check itself will be done in the Client side.

Workflow Template List Of Values Business Object
Condition to evaluate business object constant Awp0WorkflowSubmittable and limit results of dynamic LOV Awp0WorkflowTemplateLOV.
The condition checks if Awp0AddReviewer command should be visible. This condition determines if the condition Fnd0AddReviewerPrivilege evaluates to true or false.

The condition checks if Awp0AddSurrogate command should be visible. This condition determines if the selected user object represents the currently logged-in user or evaluate the Fnd0ManageSurrogatePrivilege condition for the logged-in user.

The condition checks if the Awp0NewWorkflowProcess command should be visible. This condition enables the command if the input business objects are replica objects and checked out, or not replica objects and not checked out. This will additionaly set the fnd0CurrentChangeContext property value to be null to enable the command. In addition, there is additional visibility logic on the client side to detemine the valid supported objects types to enable the command based on provider.

The condition checks if Awp0OpenInboxLocation command should be visible. This condition determines if the selected user object represents the currently logged-in user or evaluate the Fnd0AccessInboxPrivilege condition for the logged-in user.
The condition checks if Awp0OutOfOffice command should be visible. This condition determines if the selected user object represents the currently logged-in user.
This condition checks if Awp0PerformTask command should be visible. This condition determines if the logged-in user is a valid user to perform selected EPMTask or Signoff object.

The condition checks if Awp0PromoteTask command should be visible. This condition determines if the input business object is an EPMTask or Signoff and enable the Promote command based on awp0PromoteableByMeBehavior property value.

The condition checks if Awp0ReassignTask command should be visible. The condition determines if the root-task of the select object is not completed and it satisfies the Fnd0AssignTaskPrivilege condition.
The condition checks if Awp0Release command should be visible. The condition determines if the logged-in user is an active surrogate of EPMTask or Signoff object.

The condition checks if Awp0ReplaceMultipleParticipants command should be visible. This condition determines if the input business objects are either Item Revisions or sub-types of Item Revisions. In addition, there is additional visibility logic on the client side to detemine a minumum of two valid objects are selected.

The condition checks if Awp0StandIn command should be visible or not. The condition enables the command if the logged-in user is a valid surrogate and active surrogate value of EPMTask or Signoff object is not set.
The condition checks if Awp0RemoveSurrogate command should be visible. This condition determines if the logged-in user has privileges to modify the surrogate users.

The condition checks if the "Awp0ClaimTask" command should be visible. This condition determines if the condition "Fnd0AssignTaskPrivilege" evaluates to true or false, and also if the logged-in user is a member of the resource pool for EPMTask or Signoff.
Condition to check if the current user can classify the active object.
